aniDevTrap.name: aniDevTrap
aniDevTrap.contactinfo: Postal: Aperto Networks Inc 1637 S Main Street Milpitas, California 95035 Tel: +1 408 719 9977

aniDevControlTrapGeneration.name: aniDevControlTrapGeneration
aniDevControlTrapGeneration.description: Enable or disable SNMP Trap Generation.

aniDevTrapSuSyncAcquired.name: aniDevTrapSuSyncAcquired
aniDevTrapSuSyncAcquired.description: This trap is generated by LKAD when SYNC is acquired.

aniDevTrapBsuSuUp.name: aniDevTrapBsuSuUp
aniDevTrapBsuSuUp.description: This trap is sent out by BSU to report that SU is operational.

aniDevTrapBsuSuDown.name: aniDevTrapBsuSuDown
aniDevTrapBsuSuDown.description: This trap is sent out by BSU to report that SU is down.

aniDevTrapSuBsuUp.name: aniDevTrapSuBsuUp
aniDevTrapSuBsuUp.description: This trap is sent out by SU to report that BSU is operational.

aniDevTrapSuBsuDown.name: aniDevTrapSuBsuDown
aniDevTrapSuBsuDown.description: This trap is sent out by SU to report that BSU is down.

aniDevTrapDhcpFailure.name: aniDevTrapDhcpFailure
aniDevTrapDhcpFailure.description: This trap is generated when DHCP fails.

aniDevTrapConfigDownloadFailure.name: aniDevTrapConfigDownloadFailure
aniDevTrapConfigDownloadFailure.description: This trap is generated when Config file download fails.

aniDevTrapRamTooLow.name: aniDevTrapRamTooLow
aniDevTrapRamTooLow.description: This trap is sent out to indicate that the RAM is too low.

aniDevTrapRamNormal.name: aniDevTrapRamNormal
aniDevTrapRamNormal.description: This trap is sent out to indicate that the RAM available is normal. This trap is sent out to indicate that the aniDevTrapRamTooLow alarm is cleared.

aniDevTrapModemPllNotLocked.name: aniDevTrapModemPllNotLocked
aniDevTrapModemPllNotLocked.description: The Modem PLL (Phase Locked Loop) not locked trap.

aniDevTrapModemPllNotLockedClear.name: aniDevTrapModemPllNotLockedClear
aniDevTrapModemPllNotLockedClear.description: The Modem PLL (Phase Locked Loop) not locked trap cleared. This trap is sent out to indicate that the aniDevTrapModemPllNotLocked alarm is cleared.

aniDevTrapRadioVoltReg.name: aniDevTrapRadioVoltReg
aniDevTrapRadioVoltReg.description: This trap indicates a Radio Voltage Failure. It is sent out by both BSU and SU.

aniDevTrapRadioVoltRegClear.name: aniDevTrapRadioVoltRegClear
aniDevTrapRadioVoltRegClear.description: This trap is sent out when aniDevTrapRadioVoltReg (Radio Voltage Failure) alarm is cleared. It is sent out by both BSU and SU.

aniDevTrapRadioSynthNotLocked.name: aniDevTrapRadioSynthNotLocked
aniDevTrapRadioSynthNotLocked.description: This trap is generated when the Radio Synthesizer is not locked. It is sent out by BSU and SU.

aniDevTrapRadioSynthNotLockedClear.name: aniDevTrapRadioSynthNotLockedClear
aniDevTrapRadioSynthNotLockedClear.description: This trap is sent out by BSU and SU to indicate that aniDevTrapRadioSynthNotLocked is cleared.

aniDevTrapBsuFanStatus.name: aniDevTrapBsuFanStatus
aniDevTrapBsuFanStatus.description: This trap is sent out when a fan on BSU is not operational.

aniDevTrapBsuFanStatusClear.name: aniDevTrapBsuFanStatusClear
aniDevTrapBsuFanStatusClear.description: This trap is sent to indicate that aniDevTrapBsuFanStatus is cleared, that is, the fan on BSU is operational again.

aniDevTrapBsuDc12vStatus.name: aniDevTrapBsuDc12vStatus
aniDevTrapBsuDc12vStatus.description: This trap is generated when a 12V DC power failure occurs on the BSU.

aniDevTrapBsuDc12vStatusClear.name: aniDevTrapBsuDc12vStatusClear
aniDevTrapBsuDc12vStatusClear.description: This trap indicates that aniDevTrapBsuDc12vStatus alarm on the BSU has been cleared.

aniDevTrapMssPllNotLocked.name: aniDevTrapMssPllNotLocked
aniDevTrapMssPllNotLocked.description: The MSS PLL (Phase Locked Loop) not locked trap which is sent out by BSU.

aniDevTrapMssPllNotLockedClear.name: aniDevTrapMssPllNotLockedClear
aniDevTrapMssPllNotLockedClear.description: This trap indicates that aniDevTrapMssPllNotLocked alarm on the BSU has been cleared.

aniDevTrapBsuTempTooLow.name: aniDevTrapBsuTempTooLow
aniDevTrapBsuTempTooLow.description: This indicates that the temperature on the BSU is below the operating limits. A temperature sensor on the BSU checks the operating temperature of the system board.

aniDevTrapBsuTempTooHigh.name: aniDevTrapBsuTempTooHigh
aniDevTrapBsuTempTooHigh.description: This indicates that the temperature on the BSU is above the operating limits. A temperature sensor on the BSU checks the operating temperature of the system board.

aniDevTrapBsuTempNormal.name: aniDevTrapBsuTempNormal
aniDevTrapBsuTempNormal.description: This indicates that the temperature on the BSU is within the operating limits. It shows that either the aniDevTrapBsuTempTooLow or aniDevTrapBsuTempTooHigh alarm on the BSU has been cleared.

aniDevTrapFlashSpaceTooLow.name: aniDevTrapFlashSpaceTooLow
aniDevTrapFlashSpaceTooLow.description: This trap is sent out when the disk space on file system is too low. It can be sent out by either BSU or SU.

aniDevTrapFlashSpaceNormal.name: aniDevTrapFlashSpaceNormal
aniDevTrapFlashSpaceNormal.description: This trap is sent out when the disk space on file system is again normal. It can be sent out by either BSU or SU to clear the aniDevTrapFlashSpaceTooLow alarm.

aniDevTrapNvramCorrupted.name: aniDevTrapNvramCorrupted
aniDevTrapNvramCorrupted.description: This trap is sent out when the NVRAM is corrupted. 64 kB of NVRAM is allocated from the first block of flash on both BSU and SU. A checksum is maintained whenever some value if stored in it.

aniDevTrapNvramCorruptionClear.name: aniDevTrapNvramCorruptionClear
aniDevTrapNvramCorruptionClear.description: This trap indicates that aniDevTrapNvramCorrupted alarm has been cleared.

aniDevTrapFileSysCorrupted.name: aniDevTrapFileSysCorrupted
aniDevTrapFileSysCorrupted.description: This trap indicates that the file system has been corrupted. It can be sent out by either BSU or SU.

aniDevTrapFileSysCorruptionClear.name: aniDevTrapFileSysCorruptionClear
aniDevTrapFileSysCorruptionClear.description: This trap indicates that aniDevTrapFileSysCorrupted alarm has been cleared. It can be sent out by either BSU or SU.

aniDevTrapSmtpConnectFailure.name: aniDevTrapSmtpConnectFailure
aniDevTrapSmtpConnectFailure.description: This trap is sent out when the connection to the SMTP server fails. It can be sent out by either BSU or SU.

aniDevTrapSmtpDisabled.name: aniDevTrapSmtpDisabled
aniDevTrapSmtpDisabled.description: This trap is sent out when SMTP is disabled on the system (either BSU or SU).

aniDevTrapSwWatchdogReset.name: aniDevTrapSwWatchdogReset
aniDevTrapSwWatchdogReset.description: This trap is sent out when SU is reset by the Software Watchdog. The Software Watchdog feature detects low memory and task suspended cases, sends out the trap and reboots the device.

aniDevTrapNatFailure.name: aniDevTrapNatFailure
aniDevTrapNatFailure.description: This trap is sent out when NAT failure occurs. It is sent out by SU.

aniDevTrapCurrentImageCorrupted.name: aniDevTrapCurrentImageCorrupted
aniDevTrapCurrentImageCorrupted.description: This trap is sent out to indicate that the current image is corrupted. It can be sent out by both BSU or SU.

aniDevTrapBsuSuFailedReg.name: aniDevTrapBsuSuFailedReg
aniDevTrapBsuSuFailedReg.description: This trap is sent out when the BSU-SU registration fails.

aniDevTrapDefaultConfigFileNotFound.name: aniDevTrapDefaultConfigFileNotFound
aniDevTrapDefaultConfigFileNotFound.description: This trap is sent out when the default configuration file is not found. It can be sent out by both BSU or SU.

aniDevTrapCurrentBsuState.name: aniDevTrapCurrentBsuState
aniDevTrapCurrentBsuState.description: This trap shows the current BSU State.

aniDevTrapCurrentSuState.name: aniDevTrapCurrentSuState
aniDevTrapCurrentSuState.description: This trap shows the current SU State.

aniDevTrapMemBufferTooLow.name: aniDevTrapMemBufferTooLow
aniDevTrapMemBufferTooLow.description: This trap is sent out when the memory buffer is too low. It can be sent out by either BSU or SU.

aniDevTrapMemBufferNormal.name: aniDevTrapMemBufferNormal
aniDevTrapMemBufferNormal.description: This trap is sent out when the memory buffer is again normal. It can be sent out by either BSU or SU to clear the aniDevMemBufferTooLow alarm.

aniDevTrapConfigFileVersionCheckFailure.name: aniDevTrapConfigFileVersionCheckFailure
aniDevTrapConfigFileVersionCheckFailure.description: This trap is sent out when there is a problem in the version of the config file. It is sent out when either the version information is missing or if there is a mismatch in the version.

aniDevTrapDefaultFileVersionCheckFailure.name: aniDevTrapDefaultFileVersionCheckFailure
aniDevTrapDefaultFileVersionCheckFailure.description: This trap is sent out when there is a problem in the version of the default file. It is sent out when either the version information is missing or if there is a mismatch in the version.

aniDevTrapConfigFileUploadFailure.name: aniDevTrapConfigFileUploadFailure
aniDevTrapConfigFileUploadFailure.description: This trap is sent out when the upload of the config file fails.

aniDevTrapConfigFileUploadChecksumFailur.name: aniDevTrapConfigFileUploadChecksumFailure
aniDevTrapConfigFileUploadChecksumFailur.description: This trap is sent out when there is a checksum error on the config file after the upload.

aniDevTrapRunningBaselineImage.name: aniDevTrapRunningBaselineImage
aniDevTrapRunningBaselineImage.description: This trap is sent out when a baseline image is running.

aniDevTrapPowerSupplyFailure.name: aniDevTrapPowerSupplyFailure
aniDevTrapPowerSupplyFailure.description: This trap is sent out by the BSU when there is a power supply failure.

aniDevTrapPowerSupplyNormal.name: aniDevTrapPowerSupplyNormal
aniDevTrapPowerSupplyNormal.description: This trap is sent out by the BSU when the power supply is normal again. It is sent out to indicate that the aniDevTrapPowerSupplyFailure alarm is cleared.

aniDevTrapRealtimeClockFailure.name: aniDevTrapRealtimeClockFailure
aniDevTrapRealtimeClockFailure.description: This trap is sent out by the BSU when there is a real time clock failure.

aniDevTrapRealtimeClockNormal.name: aniDevTrapRealtimeClockNormal
aniDevTrapRealtimeClockNormal.description: This trap is sent out by the BSU when the real time clock is normal again. It is sent out to indicate that the aniDevTrapRealtimeClockFailure alarm is cleared.

aniDevTrapModelNumFailure.name: aniDevTrapModelNumFailure
aniDevTrapModelNumFailure.description: This trap is sent out when there is an error related to the model number.

aniDevTrapConfigParseFailure.name: aniDevTrapConfigParseFailure
aniDevTrapConfigParseFailure.description: This trap is sent out when there is an error in the parsing of the configuration file.

aniDevUpdateInventory.name: aniDevUpdateInventory
aniDevUpdateInventory.description: This trap is sent out to notify configuration change in SU customer name.

aniDevTrapPppFailure.name: aniDevTrapPppFailure
aniDevTrapPppFailure.description: This trap is sent out whenever PPP fails to establish a session.

aniDevTrapPppStatus.name: aniDevTrapPppStatus
aniDevTrapPppStatus.description: This trap is sent whenever a PPP link goes up or down.

aniDevTrapFrequencyChange.name: aniDevTrapFrequencyChange
aniDevTrapFrequencyChange.description: This trap is sent out whenever the channel frequency is changed on the BSU and SU while they are in the operational state.

aniDevTrapPPPoeSessionUp.name: aniDevTrapPPPoeSessionUp
aniDevTrapPPPoeSessionUp.description: This trap is sent out whenever the when a PPPoE Session comes up.

aniDevTrapPPPoeOfferError.name: aniDevTrapPPPoeOfferError
aniDevTrapPPPoeOfferError.description: This trap is sent out whenever the when no valid PPPoE Active Discovery Offer (PADO) is received in response to a PPPoE Active Discovery Initiation (PADI) packet or if no valid PPPoE Active Discovery Session-confirmation (PADS) is received in response to a PPPoE Active Discovery Request (PADR) packet.

aniDevTrapPPPoeSessionTerminate.name: aniDevTrapPPPoeSessionTerminate
aniDevTrapPPPoeSessionTerminate.description: This trap is sent out when a PPPoE Session is terminated.

aniDevTrapEtherAutoNegotiate.name: aniDevTrapEtherAutoNegotiate
aniDevTrapEtherAutoNegotiate.description: This trap is sent out when device go back to auto-negotiate mode.

aniDevTrapRadioInitError.name: aniDevTrapRadioInitError
aniDevTrapRadioInitError.description: This trap is sent out when the radio can't be initialized. Under an error condition this event will be generated prior to SU becoming operational.

aniDevTrapMaxPowerError.name: aniDevTrapMaxPowerError
aniDevTrapMaxPowerError.description: This trap is sent out when when the radio board can't reach maximum configured power. This can be caused by a combination of faulty (or very long) coaxial cable connecting IDU and ODU and/or extremely hot weather or just bad calibration data on the radio board.

aniDevTrapMaxPowerErrorClear.name: aniDevTrapMaxPowerErrorClear
aniDevTrapMaxPowerErrorClear.description: This trap is sent out when the event aniDevTrapMaxPowerError has been cleared.

aniDevTrapAgcTableNotCalibrated.name: aniDevTrapAgcTableNotCalibrated
aniDevTrapAgcTableNotCalibrated.description: This trap is sent out when the AGC Table is not calibrated. SODU platform relies on accurate calibration of the receive gain throughout the entire receive chain. If the table is not correctly calibrated or gets corrupted in the field, the SODU will have to fall back on default receive power adjustment algorithm, which may be far from optimal. This problem doesn't stop an SODU from getting operational but the downstream link quality can suffer.

aniDevTrapFreqTableInvalidEntry.name: aniDevTrapFreqTableInvalidEntry
aniDevTrapFreqTableInvalidEntry.description: This trap is sent out whenever the frequency table contains an invalid entry.

aniDevTrapHtmlUnzippedError.name: aniDevTrapHtmlUnzippedError
aniDevTrapHtmlUnzippedError.description: This trap is sent out when html compressed zip files are either missing or corrupted.

aniDevTrapBootLineBackupUpdated.name: aniDevTrapBootLineBackupUpdated
aniDevTrapBootLineBackupUpdated.description: This trap is sent out whenever the backup bootline parameters are updated to bring them in sync with the actual boot parameters.

aniDevTrapBootLineRestoredFromBackup.name: aniDevTrapBootLineRestoredFromBackup
aniDevTrapBootLineRestoredFromBackup.description: This trap is sent out when the main bootline parameters are corrupted and the system has to fall back on backup boot parameters.

aniDevTrapNvramBackupUpdated.name: aniDevTrapNvramBackupUpdated
aniDevTrapNvramBackupUpdated.description: This trap is sent out whenever the backup copy of NVRAM configuration parameters is updated to bring them in sync with the actual NVRAM configuration.

aniDevTrapNvramRestoredFromBackup.name: aniDevTrapNvramRestoredFromBackup
aniDevTrapNvramRestoredFromBackup.description: This trap is sent out when the main NVRAM configuration data is corrupted and the system has to fall back on backup NVRAM configuration.
